Well a lot of good things happended today.
I am student of the month for 8A for most motivated. It was fun cuz we (the other students of the months and I) got a bunch of free stuff and we got to pose for the pictures that are gonna be on display, and since we were the most motivated students we did the opposite and posed lazily.lol. it was fun and i got to take a nap on the couch in the teachers lounge lol.
I got 5 A+'s and 1 A on my report card.
My GPA is 4.275 but it's lower than my last GPA so i'm mad lol.
In typing class i typed the most words per minute in the enitire time i've been in typing! 59 words per minute with only one mistake!
Idk what else happened but today was a pretty good day considering the things listed above! lol

It's been so long since I've upodated and I finally have a second so here it goes. Yesterday our basketball team lost to Kelly. It was soo close tho. Tomorrow we play Wolfe and it's a home game so I expect to see everyone there! Lol. I'm like so bored and so lonely. Having the MEAP now sucks too. And with basketball and homework there's no time for anything else cuz on most weekends I go to work with my mom and work for like 4 hours in the a.m. and 3-4 hours in the p.m. Today basketball practice was at 7 in the morning and my alarm didn't go off and I got up at like 6:40 and my ride comes at like 6:45 so it was a really bad moning. But after school I went to the football game and I got a little hyper and it was fun. Anyway I G2G it's bedtime. Oh yea Hockey's back and I'm watching everyone of the Red Wing's Games so when there's a game on don't bug me. Lol. Only when there's a comercial or intermission. Later!

Ok so I'm finally back from deleware. It was a lot of fun. I got to meet my cousins I never met before. Well at least I got to meet one of them. The other one lives a little farther away and couldn't come down to visit. But my other cousin ,his name is J.R.,that was there is like 28 and he's married and has a son, my second cousin. J.R. is the nicest person you could meet.His wife mandy is a little shy and so is their son Elija. Elija started school the day we left for home. He's is now in 1st grade. We stayed at my aunt mary ann and uncle mike's place and spent a lot of time with them. It was so much fun. Especially when we (Mary ann,Mike,J.R.,Elija,my mom,dad and I) went to Ocean City. That was the coolest we went down to the boardwalk and went swimming in the atlantic Ocean. Anyway I have to go shopping with my mom. I'll write some other time.

You're like me! The intelligent loner. You're shy
at times but friendly, and you are never weak
and always independent. You are incredibly
intelligent (wise beyond your years) and have a
talent for many things (sports, music, art).
You have a kind and warm personality and enjoy
the simple things. Like hanging out with
friends and watching movies at home. But you're
sometimes quiet nature makes you a bit of an
outcast and a mystery to people. No matter how
pretty you are or smart or athletic, you just
can't seem to break into the crowd and be
noticed. Don't worry, try to be more outgoing
and speak out when you have more to say. Don't
hide behind your books and sports and computer,
get out there and get noticed. You also have
deep desires in life and feel vunerable and
alone at times. Don't feel sad either, What
helps me to express feelings and dreams that I
can't say to people, is through my writting.
Maybe you should try.

Today at CKC half of us went to the soup kitchen while the other half went to play basketball. At the oup kitchen we went to one of the gardens and again we split up into groups. I picked the lettuce stalks and killed these big spiders, that was kinda fun. Even though I felt like a dork steping on the spiders and screaming at the same time.  Any way, then I TRIED to pick oakra (however you spell it) but I wasn't doing very well at that so sarah and alyson. That didn't take long so after that we started picking berries or something. I don't remember what they're called. That was really fun. I never knew that picking berries, or whatever, could be so much fun. And on the way back we went by this house that was covered with stuffed animals and dolls that were like nailed to the house or something but it kinda freaked me out a little bit. Anyway it was an awesome day, but I gotta go enjoy the rest of it.

My dad came home early from his hunting trip and he got about a 200 lb  female black bear and made it into a rug. He got so much meat it filled 1/3 of the huge freezer we have downstairs! I'm wondering if he'll eat it all. The other two guys he went with also got bears but one of them only got a little cub bear so nothing much to celebrate about that. I feal kinda sorry that it was only a youngster though. When my dad got home at 7am he slept until 6:00pm. Almost 12hours straight but I can't blame him after being awake for 28 hours including the 12hour drive home! I would've fell asleep at the wheel. At first when my dad never called I was worried that something happened to hime because no one told me he called the first day! Well other than that  nothing much happened.

Well My dad left for his trip at eleven last night. I gave him a little note to read when he gets there and a little present. Since he is going to Canada I gave him all of my canadian change I had been saving. But ever since like a week or two ago I've been having this feeling that something bad is going to happen. And I can't seem to get rid of it until my dad is back here where I can see he's not injured. 
But to try and keep my mind off things I have been writing a book and it's similar to a dream I had a few days ago. And when daddy left he gave mom some money take me to the theatre. Well that's it for this entry. Later

Okay so mom finally went to the dentist after all of these years and today she got a root canal and a tooth pulled. I know you're thinking ooowwww right? She came back just fine no pain at all.In fact the first day she went there this 4yr old had a root canal  and he came out smiling and laughing! I couldn't believe it! So from now on I'm going to that dentist because I'm a wuss when it comes to pain! I hate needles. My mom's Birthday is coming up soon. I don't know what to get her. I didn't save much money but I have to decide fast so I know where to go to the present. I wish it was easy shopping for people. I'll write more soon after the sleep over mom planned with Alyssa on Wednsday. Alyssa only about 4 or 5 and it's her first sleepover at someone's house besides her family. This should be interesting. I hope it goes well.
